@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Trapezik" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench
must have at least 4 colours.

                             How to play?

  'Trapezik' consists of a 9 by 9 tile game board in which there are
5 square 'rings' that are nestled one inside the other. In each ring
a number of diagonal bars are randomly turned and between those bars,
depending on how the bars are placed, there are coloured trapezes. The
ring borders act as widest and the narrowest part of the trapezes and
the diagonal bars are used for the sides of the trapezes.

  To play, click on any diagonal bar in the game board, but beware: as
you click on one diagonal bar, another bar may turn randomly just to
complicate the game a bit. When two diagonal bars are placed correctly,
a coloured trapeze will appear between the two bars. Continue turning
the diagonal bars until you get 52 trapezes.

  Note that the game board is arranged in such a way that a total of 52
trapezes and 8 parallelograms can be created, their position have no
importance, but when the total number of each figure is obtained, the
game is won.

  Have fun!

OPTIONS

  You can restart the game anytime by clicking on the @{b}Restart@{ub} button.

  The colour of the trapezes can be changed by clicking on any trapeze
that appear on the game board.

  Press the 'Esc' key to quit the game.

